tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine, significant proteinuria, and high urinary ketones, suggesting acute or chronic renal dysfunction with possible nephrotic-range proteinuria and ketosis. Urine is brown, cloudy, and has low specific gravity, indicating possible renal concentrating defect. Blood glucose and HbA1c are low, arguing against diabetes. No evidence of urinary infection. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation for renal impairment and further assessment of proteinuria and ketonuria.
